member.remarks: As per the standard, contributory properties are neither normative nor informative, but are used to derive .

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.AsciiHexDigit
member.remarks: ASCII characters commonly used for the representation of hexadecimal numbers.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.BidiControl
member.remarks: Format control characters which have specific functions in the Unicode Bidirectional Algorithm [UAX9].

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Dash
member.remarks: Punctuation characters explicitly called out as dashes in the Unicode Standard, plus their compatibility equivalents. Most of these have the General_Category value Pd, but some have the General_Category value Sm because of their use in mathematics.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Deprecated
member.remarks: For a machine-readable list of deprecated characters. No characters will ever be removed from the standard, but the usage of deprecated characters is strongly discouraged.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Diacritic
member.remarks: Characters that linguistically modify the meaning of another character to which they apply. Some diacritics are not combining characters, and some combining characters are not diacritics.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Extender
member.remarks: Characters whose principal function is to extend the value or shape of a preceding alphabetic character. Typical of these are length and iteration marks.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.HexDigit
member.remarks: Characters commonly used for the representation of hexadecimal numbers, plus their compatibility equivalents.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Hyphen
member.remarks: Dashes which are used to mark connections between pieces of words, plus the Katakana middle dot. The Katakana middle dotfunctions like a hyphen, but is shaped like a dot rather than a dash.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Ideographic
member.remarks: Characters considered to be CJKV (Chinese, Japanese, Korean, and Vietnamese) ideographs. This property roughly defines the class of "Chinese characters" and does not include characters of other logographic scripts such as Cuneiform or Egyptian Hieroglyphs.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.IdsBinaryOperator
member.remarks: Used in Ideographic Description Sequences.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.IdsTrinaryOperator
member.remarks: Used in Ideographic Description Sequences.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.JoinControl
member.remarks: Format control characters which have specific functions for control of cursive joining and ligation.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.LogicalOrderException
member.remarks: A small number of spacing vowel letters occurring in certain Southeast Asian scripts such as Thai and Lao, which use a visual order display model. These letters are stored in text ahead of syllable-initial consonants, and require special handling for processes such as searching and sorting.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.NonCharacterCodePoint
member.remarks: Code points permanently reserved for internal use.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.OtherAlphabetic

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.QuotationMark
member.remarks: Punctuation characters that function as quotation marks.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.Radical
member.remarks: Used in Ideographic Description Sequences.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.SoftDotted
member.remarks: Characters with a "soft dot", like i or j. An accent placed on these characters causes the dot to disappear. An explicit dot abovecan be added where required, such as in Lithuanian.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.SequenceTerminal
member.remarks: Sentence Terminal. Used in Unicode Standard Annex #29, "Unicode Text Segmentation" [UAX29].

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.TerminalPunctuation
member.remarks: Punctuation characters that generally mark the end of textual units.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.UnifiedIdeograph
member.remarks: A property which specifies the exact set of Unified CJK Ideographs in the standard. This set excludes CJK Compatibility Ideographs (which have canonical decompositions to Unified CJK Ideographs), as well as characters from the CJK Symbols and Punctuation block. The property is used in the definition of Ideographic Description Sequences.

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.VariationSelector
member.remarks: Indicates characters that are Variation Selectors. For details on the behavior of these characters, seeStandardizedVariants.html, Section 23.4, Variation Selectors in [Unicode], and Unicode Technical Standard #37, "Unicode Ideographic Variation Database" [UTS37].

member.name: F:System.Unicode.ContributoryProperties.WhiteSpace
member.remarks: Spaces, separator characters and other control characters which should be treated by programming languages as "white space" for the purpose of parsing elements. See also Line_Break, Grapheme_Cluster_Break, Sentence_Break, and Word_Break, which classify space characters and related controls somewhat differently for particular text segmentation contexts.
